com.nokia.places

Interface ExternalLink


  • public interface ExternalLink
    This interface represents a link to the origin of supplied information, which typically is a website of the supplier.

    Note: By default, client devices open a web browser whenever a user wants to follow an ExternalLink. Applications might want to check the MIME type attribute of the link to see if there is a better user agent than a web browser for handling the media type of the linked resource.


    See Also:
    Nokia's Restful Places API - Links

    • Method Detail

      • getTitle

        java.lang.String getTitle()
        This method retrieves the localized title for the resource to which the link refers. Client devices can display a title within the application that calls this method.

        Note: A title for a resource targeted by an external link is optional. A call to this method could return null.

        Returns:
        The title for the external link (could be null).

      • getId

        java.lang.String getId()
        This method retrieves the unique identifier for the resource to which the external link refers.

        Note: An ID for a resource targeted by an external link is optional. A call to this method could return null.

        Returns:
        The identifier for the resource to which the external link refers (could be null).

      • getIcon

        javax.microedition.lcdui.Image getIcon()
        This method retrieves the link to the icon for the resource to which the external link refers.

        Note: An icon for a resource targeted by an external link is optional. A call to this method could return null.

        Returns:
        An javax.microedition.lcdui.Image representing the associated icon for the linked resource if one exists, null otherwise.

      • getUri

        java.lang.String getUri()
        This method retrieves the URI of the resource to which the external link refers.
        Returns:
        The URI for an external link.

      • getMimeType

        java.lang.String getMimeType()
        This method retrieves the MIME type of the resource to which the link refers.

        Note: A MIME type for a resource targeted by an external link is optional. A call to this method could return null. If missing, the link refers to an unspecified web resource, where it is best opened in a universal HTTP user agent such as a web browser.

        Returns:
        The MIME type of the external resource (could be null).
